docs.abstract: The executive, known as an Emmy magnet before leaving HBO in February, is in talks to make shows for a new streaming service.
docs.snippet: The executive, known as an Emmy magnet before leaving HBO in February, is in talks to make shows for a new streaming service.
docs.lead_paragraph: Richard Plepler was an Emmy magnet when he was in charge of HBO, with a knack for betting on shows that pleased critics and added subscribers. Now he is in the final stages of talks to produce television shows and documentaries for the new Apple TV Plus streaming service, according to two people with knowledge of the talks.

headline.main: Richard Plepler, Former HBO Boss, Is Close to Apple Deal
headline.print_headline: Ex-HBO Chief, Known As Magnet for Emmys, Is Close to Apple Deal

docs.abstract: Amid last summer’s recession fever, we identified the key indicators to watch for signs of trouble. Five months later, the situation has improved, but risks remain.
docs.snippet: Amid last summer’s recession fever, we identified the key indicators to watch for signs of trouble. Five months later, the situation has improved, but risks remain.
docs.lead_paragraph: For a few weeks last summer, you would have been forgiven for thinking the United States was racing headlong into a recession. Financial markets were in turmoil, once-confident business leaders were suddenly jittery and seemingly every financial news outlet was warning that the economy was in trouble.

headline.main: A Recession Hasn’t Arrived (Yet). Here’s Where You’ll See It First.
headline.print_headline: Most of the Warning Signs Of Recession Have Eased

docs.abstract: A year and a half into the trade war, China seems to have a winning strategy: Stay tough and let the Trump administration negotiate with itself.
docs.snippet: A year and a half into the trade war, China seems to have a winning strategy: Stay tough and let the Trump administration negotiate with itself.
docs.lead_paragraph: BEIJING — President Trump’s initial retreat from his trade-war threats has handed hard-liners in China a victory. A longer, pricklier trade war and stiff Chinese resistance to economic reforms could result.

headline.main: China’s Hard-Liners Win a Round in Trump’s Trade Deal
headline.print_headline: China Trade Hawks Win A Round From Trump
